text: Michèle Victory (born 1958) is a French politician for the Socialist Party and a member of the French National Assembly for Ardèche's 2nd constituency. She was first a substitute candidate in 2007 and became a member of the assembly in December 2017. On 9 March 2020, during the 2019–20 coronavirus pandemic, she tested positive for the virus. ==References== Category:1958 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes Category:People from Ardèche
